itemLabel: Susan Williams, Baroness Williams of Trafford

wikipedia_page.main: Susan Frances Maria Williams, Baroness Williams of Trafford (née McElroy; formerly Fildes; born 16 May 1967) is a junior minister in the Government of the United Kingdom and a Conservative life peer.

response: *  1967   – Susan Williams, Baroness Williams of Trafford, British politician

link_mentions.page: List of barons in the peerages of Britain and Ireland

response: He served as an Opposition spokesman on various subjects; immediately prior to the 2010 general election he was spokesman for transport and an Opposition whip. Following the Conservative victory in that election Earl Attlee was appointed a Lord-in-waiting or Government whip in the House of Lords. He continued in that role until April 2014, when he left the government. He was replaced by Susan Williams, Baroness Williams of Trafford.
